{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":255017,"duration_api_ms":254683,"num_turns":3,"result":"Here's a summary of what the analysis found:\n\n## tests/edge/ — Analysis Summary\n\n**8 test files, 43 total tests** targeting adversarial inputs across 6 failure domains.\n\n### What's here\n\n| File | Tests | Focus |\n|---|---|---|\n| `corrupt_state.bats` | 8 | Malformed JSON, cost file parsing bugs, nullglob regression |\n| `numeric_edge_cases.bats` | 9 | Budget arithmetic boundaries, non-numeric inputs, zero budgets |\n| `empty_json.bats` | 7 | Null values, missing keys, 0-byte files, invalid JSON |\n| `special_characters.bats` | 7 | Apostrophes/parens in prompts (the PR #2 regression), paths with spaces |\n| `validation_regex.bats` | 4 | Two documented regex bugs in `validate_claude_md` |\n| `cost_reporting.bats` | 4 | Phase grouping and zero-cost filtering in `print_cost_summary` |\n| `budget_exhaustion.bats` | 2 | Agents skipping when budget already/mid-run exceeded |\n| `cli_args.bats` | 2 | `--help` / `-h` flags on the main script |\n\n### Key gotchas\n\n1. **Nullglob is always active in tests** — `_common_setup` sources `synthesize.sh` which sets `shopt -s nullglob` globally. The regression test in `corrupt_state.bats` guards against `cat *.cost` blocking on stdin when no cost files exist.\n\n2. **DOCUMENTS BUG pattern** — several tests deliberately assert the *buggy* behavior (e.g., cost files without pipe delimiters cause spending to be silently ignored; prohibition regex requires trailing space so `\"Don't\"` at end-of-line isn't detected). These are intentional bug registries.\n\n3. **bc produces `.20` not `0.20`** — tests for budget values < 1 must accept both forms.\n\n4. **`@file` prompt syntax** is the fix for PR #2 — `special_characters.bats` is the regression test for apostrophes in developer answers breaking parallel agent script generation.\n\n5. **Defaults must be set before sourcing libs** in `_common_setup` — lib files evaluate `${VAR:-default}` at source time.","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"8aadeddb-ed5c-48d0-bec1-9e645ee2327d","total_cost_usd":0.43676,"usage":{"input_tokens":7,"cache_creation_input_tokens":30485,"cache_read_input_tokens":77164,"output_tokens":6343,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":30485,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[{"input_tokens":1,"output_tokens":571,"cache_read_input_tokens":37516,"cache_creation_input_tokens":5031,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":5031},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-sonnet-4-6":{"inputTokens":7,"outputTokens":6343,"cacheReadInputTokens":77164,"cacheCreationInputTokens":30485,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.23263394999999998,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":32000},"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001":{"inputTokens":122,"outputTokens":12204,"cacheReadInputTokens":765003,"cacheCreationInputTokens":53187,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.20412604999999998,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":32000}},"permission_denials":[],"structured_output":{"module_path":"tests/edge/","purpose":"Edge-case test suite for ultrainit's most fragile boundaries: budget exhaustion, CLI argument parsing, corrupt/malformed state, special characters in prompts, and regex validation bugs. Tests deliberately document known bugs as current behavior rather than asserting correctness, serving as both regression guards and a bug registry.","architecture":{"overview":"Eight bats-core test files organized by failure domain rather than by source module. Each file targets one category of adversarial input or boundary condition. Tests range from unit-level (single function with crafted input) to near-integration (running run_agents_parallel with mock Claude). All tests share common setup/teardown from tests/helpers/test_helper.bash. About half the files install the mock Claude binary via mock_claude.bash; the other half test pure functions that don't call Claude.","subdirectories":[],"data_flow":"Each test: (1) calls _common_setup to create TEST_TMPDIR/WORK_DIR/TARGET_DIR with directory structure and source all libs; (2) optionally calls setup_mock_claude to prepend a mock claude binary to PATH; (3) directly invokes lib functions or the main ultrainit.sh script; (4) asserts on exit codes, file existence, or output content; (5) _common_teardown removes TEST_TMPDIR. Cost files flow as phase|agent|cost text in $WORK_DIR/costs/*.cost. Mock responses flow from MOCK_CLAUDE_RESPONSE or MOCK_CLAUDE_DISPATCH_DIR files through the mock binary to run_agent's stdout capture."},"key_files":[{"path":"tests/edge/corrupt_state.bats","purpose":"Most comprehensive edge file. Tests resilience to malformed state.json, cost files without pipe delimiters (silent spending loss bug), and the critical nullglob regression: when synthesize.sh sets shopt -s nullglob globally, cat *.cost with no matching files blocks on stdin forever. Contains 8 tests, several explicitly marked as bug documentation.","importance":"critical"},{"path":"tests/edge/special_characters.bats","purpose":"Regression tests for the real bug (PR #2) where apostrophes and parentheses in developer answers broke shell quoting in parallel agent scripts. Verifies the @file prompt fix — that prompts are written to temp files and read with @ syntax to bypass shell interpolation. Also tests paths with spaces and skill names with slashes.","importance":"critical"},{"path":"tests/edge/numeric_edge_cases.bats","purpose":"9 tests covering every numeric boundary in the budget system: empty/non-numeric TOTAL_BUDGET defaults, negative agent counts, division-by-near-zero, zero budget with/without spending, and check_budget_sanity thresholds. Exercises compute_budgets, set_agent_budget, check_budget, and check_budget_sanity from lib/config.sh.","importance":"critical"},{"path":"tests/edge/validation_regex.bats","purpose":"Documents two bugs in validate_claude_md: the prohibition regex '(never |don.t |do not )' requires trailing spaces, so 'Don't' or 'Never' at end-of-line are not detected. 4 tests. Tests assert current (buggy) behavior to prevent silent regression if the bug is fixed without updating tests.","importance":"important"},{"path":"tests/edge/budget_exhaustion.bats","purpose":"2 tests for budget enforcement: agent skipping when budget already exceeded (by pre-populating cost files above TOTAL_BUDGET), and sequential agents halting mid-phase as cumulative spending crosses the limit.","importance":"important"},{"path":"tests/edge/empty_json.bats","purpose":"7 tests for JSON parsing resilience: null values, missing keys, empty arrays, 0-byte files, and invalid JSON mixed with valid JSON. Exercises validate_claude_md, write_artifacts, merge_settings, and build_docs_context. Key finding: jq -r '.key' on missing key returns the string 'null', which wc -l counts as 1 line — validation fails gracefully but doesn't crash.","importance":"important"},{"path":"tests/edge/cost_reporting.bats","purpose":"4 tests for print_cost_summary: phase grouping, zero-cost filtering, multi-phase aggregation. Tests the guard on utils.sh:134 where entries with cost '0' are skipped — note '0.0' does NOT match '0', which may be unintended.","importance":"reference"},{"path":"tests/edge/cli_args.bats","purpose":"Minimal: 2 tests verifying --help and -h both exit 0 and print 'Usage'. Tests the main ultrainit.sh entry point rather than library functions.","importance":"reference"},{"path":"tests/helpers/test_helper.bash","purpose":"Universal setup: loads bats-support/bats-assert/bats-file, defines _common_setup (creates tmpdir hierarchy, sets all defaults BEFORE sourcing libs to honor ${VAR:-default} patterns, sources all libs), _common_teardown, source_lib, use_fixture, and make_claude_envelope (creates valid Claude API response envelopes for mocking).","importance":"critical"},{"path":"tests/helpers/mock_claude.bash","purpose":"Installs a fake claude binary at the front of PATH. Supports single-response mode (MOCK_CLAUDE_RESPONSE), per-agent dispatch mode (MOCK_CLAUDE_DISPATCH_DIR with files keyed by agent name), exit code control (MOCK_CLAUDE_EXIT_CODE), and call logging (MOCK_CLAUDE_LOG). Handles 'claude auth status' specially. Used by ~50% of edge tests.","importance":"critical"}],"patterns":[{"name":"Bug Documentation Tests","description":"Tests assert current buggy behavior rather than ideal behavior, serving as a bug registry. Comments mark tests with 'DOCUMENTS BUG' or 'PREDICTION'. This prevents silent regression if a bug is fixed — the test will fail and force a deliberate update. Example: corrupt_state.bats test 4 asserts that cost files without pipe delimiters cause spending to be silently ignored by awk's $3 field parsing.","example_files":["tests/edge/corrupt_state.bats","tests/edge/validation_regex.bats"]},{"name":"Manual State Injection","description":"Rather than running agents to create cost files or state, tests write raw files directly: 'echo \"gather|identity|3.00\" > $WORK_DIR/costs/identity.cost'. This lets tests set up exact boundary conditions (e.g., $6.00 spent against a $5.00 budget) without API calls. State.json is pre-written as corrupt JSON or populated JSON as needed.","example_files":["tests/edge/budget_exhaustion.bats","tests/edge/corrupt_state.bats","tests/edge/cost_reporting.bats"]},{"name":"Nullglob Regression Guards","description":"Two tests explicitly enable 'shopt -s nullglob' before testing functions, mirroring the real runtime condition set by synthesize.sh. This catches the class of bug where '*.cost' expanding to nothing causes 'cat *.cost' to block on stdin. Tests use a timeout or subshell with 'run' to detect hangs.","example_files":["tests/edge/corrupt_state.bats"]},{"name":"bc Arithmetic Tolerance","description":"Budget calculations use bc which can produce '.20' instead of '0.20'. Tests explicitly accept both forms: '[[ \"$AGENT_BUDGET\" == \".20\" || \"$AGENT_BUDGET\" == \"0.20\" ]]'. This pattern appears wherever set_agent_budget output is checked.","example_files":["tests/edge/numeric_edge_cases.bats"]},{"name":"@file Prompt Bypass","description":"The fix for special character handling (PR #2): when a prompt starts with @, agent.sh reads it from the file rather than expanding it as a shell argument. Tests verify this by creating prompts containing apostrophes, parentheses, and dollar signs, then asserting run_agent and run_agents_parallel succeed and produce findings files. The temp-script approach in run_agents_parallel bakes variable values as literals, so @file avoids re-interpolation.","example_files":["tests/edge/special_characters.bats"]},{"name":"All-Libs Source Pattern","description":"_common_setup sources ALL lib files together (utils.sh, config.sh, agent.sh, gather.sh, research.sh, synthesize.sh, validate.sh, merge.sh) rather than only the lib under test. This intentionally tests cross-library side effects like nullglob being set by synthesize.sh affecting glob patterns in config.sh.","example_files":["tests/helpers/test_helper.bash"]}],"conventions":{"naming":"Test files are named by failure domain, not by source module: budget_exhaustion.bats, corrupt_state.bats, special_characters.bats. Test names describe the input condition and expected outcome: 'check_budget handles cost file with no pipe delimiters'. Helper functions local to a test file are prefixed with underscore: _make_output().","imports":"Every test file starts with 'load ../helpers/test_helper' then 'load ../helpers/mock_claude' (if needed). _common_setup is called in every setup(). Libs are sourced inside _common_setup via the PROJECT_ROOT-relative path 'source $PROJECT_ROOT/lib/X.sh'.","error_handling":"Tests use 'run command' to capture exit codes into $status without aborting the test. Direct function calls (without 'run') are used when the test expects success and wants clean stderr. assert_success/assert_failure check $status. Fine-grained checks use [[ ... ]] directly for numeric comparisons or string matching.","other":["Cost file format: 'phase|agent|cost' — three pipe-delimited fields, one file per agent in $WORK_DIR/costs/","make_claude_envelope signature: make_claude_envelope '{json}' [cost_usd] [is_error_bool] — wraps structured output in the real claude -p --output-format json envelope","Defaults are set BEFORE sourcing libs in _common_setup so ${VAR:-default} expressions in lib files honor test values","Tests that don't use mock_claude skip the setup_mock_claude call entirely; no mock binary is installed","NON_INTERACTIVE is always 'true' in test setup to skip the developer questions phase"]},"dependencies":{"internal":["lib/config.sh — compute_budgets, set_agent_budget, check_budget, get_remaining_budget, check_budget_sanity, setup_work_dir","lib/agent.sh — run_agent, run_agents_parallel, record_cost","lib/utils.sh — print_cost_summary, mark_phase_complete, is_phase_complete","lib/validate.sh — validate_claude_md","lib/merge.sh — write_artifacts, merge_settings","lib/synthesize.sh — build_docs_context (and nullglob side effect)","lib/gather.sh — safe_name sed formula","lib/research.sh — domain-research prompt building","ultrainit.sh — CLI argument parsing and usage()"],"external_key":[{"name":"bats-core","purpose":"Test runner framework — @test blocks, setup/teardown, run wrapper"},{"name":"bats-assert","purpose":"assert_success, assert_failure, assert_output --partial"},{"name":"bats-support","purpose":"Formatting support for bats-assert error messages"},{"name":"bats-file","purpose":"assert_file_exists, assert_file_not_exists"},{"name":"jq","purpose":"Creating test JSON fixtures inline with jq -n and extracting values for assertions"},{"name":"bc","purpose":"Arithmetic in tests matching production budget calculations"},{"name":"Docker","purpose":"Isolation layer — tests run inside Dockerfile.test image; make test-edge runs docker run"}]},"domain_terms":[{"term":"envelope","meaning":"The JSON wrapper returned by 'claude -p --output-format json': {is_error, total_cost_usd, structured_output}. make_claude_envelope creates these for mocking."},{"term":"dispatch mode","meaning":"Mock Claude behavior where per-agent response files are looked up by agent name in MOCK_CLAUDE_DISPATCH_DIR, enabling different agents to return different mock data in the same test run."},{"term":"cost file","meaning":"A file in $WORK_DIR/costs/{agent}.cost containing 'phase|agent|cost_usd'. One file per agent to avoid write-race conditions in parallel execution."},{"term":"nullglob","meaning":"A bash shell option (shopt -s nullglob) set by synthesize.sh that causes glob patterns with no matches to expand to nothing instead of the literal pattern string. Creates a class of bug where 'cat *.cost' with no .cost files blocks on stdin."},{"term":"DOCUMENTS BUG","meaning":"Comment marker in test files indicating the test asserts current buggy behavior. The test passes when the bug is present; it will fail if the bug is fixed, forcing deliberate test update."},{"term":"@file prompt","meaning":"When a prompt string starts with '@', agent.sh reads it from the file path that follows, bypassing shell argument interpolation. The fix for the special characters bug (PR #2)."},{"term":"safe_name","meaning":"A sanitized version of a directory path used as an agent name and findings filename. Generated by sed: slashes→dashes, dots→dashes, parens removed, empty→'root'."},{"term":"phase budget","meaning":"A fraction of TOTAL_BUDGET allocated to one phase: 50% gather, 10% research, 30% synthesize, 10% validate. Stored in GATHER_BUDGET, RESEARCH_BUDGET, etc."},{"term":"AGENT_BUDGET","meaning":"The per-agent spending limit passed as --max-budget-usd to each claude -p call. Computed as phase_budget / agent_count by set_agent_budget."}],"gotchas":[{"issue":"synthesize.sh sets 'shopt -s nullglob' globally. When sourced (as _common_setup does), this affects ALL subsequent glob expansions in the test process, including inside config.sh's check_budget. 'cat *.cost' with no .cost files will block on stdin forever.","solution":"The production fix guards with array expansion: files=($WORK_DIR/costs/*.cost); [[ ${#files[@]} -eq 0 ]] && return 0. The regression test in corrupt_state.bats verifies this. If you add new glob-based file iteration in lib files, always guard against empty expansion."},{"issue":"Cost files without pipe delimiters cause spending to be silently ignored. awk -F'|' '{ sum += $3 }' treats $3 as empty (0) when there are no pipes. A bare '50.00' in a cost file contributes nothing to the budget check.","solution":"Always write cost files as 'phase|agent|cost' with two pipe separators. This is a known, documented bug (corrupt_state.bats test 4). Do not write cost files manually in production code paths."},{"issue":"The prohibition detection regex in validate_claude_md is '(never |don.t |do not )' with trailing spaces. 'Never' or 'Don't' at end-of-line have no trailing space and are not matched. Prohibition-heavy CLAUDE.md content ending sentences with these words will fail to increment prohibition_count.","solution":"Known bug, documented in validation_regex.bats. The fix would be to use '\\b' word boundaries or remove trailing spaces from the pattern. Until fixed, ensure prohibitions are in mid-sentence positions during synthesis."},{"issue":"bc can produce '.20' instead of '0.20' for values less than 1. String comparisons like '[[ \"$AGENT_BUDGET\" == \"0.20\" ]]' will fail.","solution":"Always accept both forms in test assertions: '[[ \"$x\" == \".20\" || \"$x\" == \"0.20\" ]]'. In production code, pipe through 'printf %.2f' if you need normalized format."},{"issue":"jq -r '.missing_key' returns the string 'null' (not empty string). wc -l counts it as 1 line. validate_claude_md will see a 1-line CLAUDE.md and fail with 'too thin' rather than a null-specific error.","solution":"Use jq -e and check exit code, or use '// empty' to get empty string for missing keys. Tests in empty_json.bats document this behavior."},{"issue":"The safe_name sed formula removes parentheses and slashes but does NOT remove spaces. A directory named 'src (old copy)' becomes 'src old copy' with spaces, which would break agent file names used as bash variables or filenames without quoting.","solution":"Potential bug documented in special_characters.bats. If adding new directory name handling, ensure spaces are also removed or replaced with dashes in safe_name generation."},{"issue":"_common_setup sources ALL lib files including synthesize.sh even when only testing config.sh functions. The nullglob side effect is always active in tests. This is intentional (tests cross-lib interactions) but means you cannot test glob behavior in isolation without explicitly unsetting nullglob.","solution":"If a test needs clean glob behavior, add 'shopt -u nullglob' explicitly at the start of that test. Remember to restore it in teardown."},{"issue":"Defaults must be set BEFORE sourcing libs in _common_setup. Lib files use '${VAR:-default}' patterns evaluated at source time. If you add a new env var in a lib file and it has a default, set it in _common_setup before the source block or tests will use the lib's default rather than the test's intended value.","solution":"Add all new configurable env vars to the defaults block in tests/helpers/test_helper.bash (_common_setup lines 29-43) when introducing them to any lib file."}],"skill_opportunities":[{"name":"add-edge-test","description":"Scaffold a new edge test file for a given failure domain. Generates the correct bats header, setup/teardown with _common_setup, optional mock_claude loading, and placeholder @test blocks following the bug-documentation pattern.","workflow_steps":["Identify which lib functions the edge case targets","Determine if mock_claude is needed (agent execution) or not (pure functions)","Create tests/edge/{domain}.bats with standard header and setup/teardown","Add @test blocks with run wrappers, manual state injection, and appropriate assertions","Add make target or verify existing 'make test-edge' covers the new file"]}],"commands":[{"command":"make test-edge","purpose":"Run only the tests/edge/ suite inside the Docker test container"},{"command":"make test-all","purpose":"Run unit + scripts + edge + integration tests in Docker"},{"command":"make test-image","purpose":"Build the local Docker test image (one-time or after Dockerfile.test changes)"},{"command":"docker run --rm -v $(pwd):/app ultrainit-test bats tests/edge/corrupt_state.bats","purpose":"Run a single edge test file in Docker for rapid iteration"}]},"terminal_reason":"completed","fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"d4101ec1-ad51-4e5f-95ad-99a1c4c728ce"}
